Transcription.Text: Lace became the servant of vanity and lent its rich decoration to robes and dresses and one thinks particularly of the extravagant Eliza- bethan ruffs and Carolean collars. Under Cromwell lace was dismissed as ungodly - at least for the middle and lower classes.
